[I wonder if we will be hearing more about human cases from those in
contact with this mare - Mod.TG
[This virus continues to fascinate. Little or no disease in horses; none
or rare transmission from horse to horse; the unfortunate and rare
transmission from horse to human; no transmission between humans. This
virus must be barely hanging on in nature (flying foxes) but somehow
maintained between flying foxes. Are there any experimental transmission
data with flying foxes? Early studies of rabies in bats might serve as
models for such studies. Rick Steece and I were fortunate enough to
isolate a strain of rabies virus from fetal bat tissues ( Steece, R. and
C.H. Calisher. Isolation of rabies virus from fetal tissues of _Tadarida
braziliensis_. J. Wildl. Dis. 25:329-334, 1989); someone might look at
fetal flying fox tissues and perhaps get lucky. - Mod CHC
.....................................................tg/chc/jw

